'''Examplia''' is a fictional [[terrestrial planet]] used here as a ''representative''
wikitext sample for benchmarking.<ref name="primary">Authored for the wikrs test suite.</ref>
It is the [[Star system|third world]] from its star and is not to be confused with
[[Examplia (disambiguation)|the moon of the same name]].<!-- editor note: keep this neutral -->

== History ==
The name first appeared in <nowiki>[[brackets]]</nowiki> in early drafts. For more
detail see the [https://example.org/examplia external overview] or the
[https://example.org bare link].

=== Formation ===
Examplia formed from the [[protoplanetary disk]] approximately 4.5&nbsp;billion years
ago. Key stages included:

* Accretion of [[planetesimal]]s
* Differentiation into a metallic [[planetary core|core]] and silicate mantle
* Late heavy bombardment, recorded in its [[File:Examplia-craters.jpg|thumb|right|Heavily cratered southern highlands]] cratered terrain

